36#include "kadm5_locl.h"
37
38__RCSID("$NetBSD: delete_s.c,v 1.2 2017/01/28 21:31:49 christos Exp $");
39
40kadm5_ret_t
41kadm5_s_delete_principal(void *server_handle, krb5_principal princ)
42{
43 kadm5_server_context *context = server_handle;
44 kadm5_ret_t ret;
45 hdb_entry_ex ent;
46
47 memset(&ent, 0, sizeof(ent));
48 if (!context->keep_open) {
49 ret = context->db->hdb_open(context->context, context->db, O_RDWR, 0);
50 if(ret) {
51 krb5_warn(context->context, ret, "opening database");
52 return ret;
53 }
54 }
55
56 ret = kadm5_log_init(context);
57 if (ret)
58 goto out;
59
60 ret = context->db->hdb_fetch_kvno(context->context, context->db, princ,
61 HDB_F_DECRYPT|HDB_F_GET_ANY|HDB_F_ADMIN_DATA, 0, &ent);
62 if (ret == HDB_ERR_NOENTRY)
63 goto out2;
64 if (ent.entry.flags.immutable) {
65 ret = KADM5_PROTECT_PRINCIPAL;
66 goto out3;
67 }
68
69 ret = hdb_seal_keys(context->context, context->db, &ent.entry);
70 if (ret)
71 goto out3;
72
73 /* This logs the change for iprop and writes to the HDB */
74 ret = kadm5_log_delete(context, princ);
75
76 out3:
77 hdb_free_entry(context->context, &ent);
78 out2:
79 (void) kadm5_log_end(context);
80 out:
81 if (!context->keep_open) {
82 kadm5_ret_t ret2;
83 ret2 = context->db->hdb_close(context->context, context->db);
84 if (ret == 0 && ret2 != 0)
85 ret = ret2;
86 }
87 return _kadm5_error_code(ret);
88}
